translator.expression
Interface Domain

All Known Subinterfaces:
ConstantDomain, ExpressionDomain, ExpressionRange, IntRange
All Known Implementing Classes:
BoolDomain, BoundedExpressionRange, BoundedIntRange, IdentifierDomain, MultipleExpressionRange, MultipleIntRange, SparseExpressionRange, SparseIntRange
public interface Domain

This interface represents Domains: domains are given in correspondence with a decision variable or quantified variables.

Method Detail

evaluate

Domain evaluate()
Evaluate all the expressions in this domain. This concerns mainly evaluation of lower and upper bounds, for instance. If all expressions int the domain can be reduced to integer values, the domain is supposed to be transformed to an IntRange (or MixedIntRange, respectively).
